reviewText: I thought this was a CD, guess I didn't read the description properly.  Great music, great sound and some interesting family history and picturesque shots.  I don't have much time to watch DVD's like this but its worth the time and effort. Something to do on a lazy Sunday afternoon with family around.
summary: Great DVD that I thought was a CD!

reviewText: Note: The reason this review is in capital letters, is because, at the time, that I wrote the review, I did not know, it was not proper computer etiquette, to write in capital letters. Also, my eyes are not all that great, so capital letters are easier for me to read. However, please read it anyway, and I hope it will be helpful. Thanks. SO, HERE WE GO, "SHOUT IT, SHOUT IT OUT LOUD": THIS IS AN EXCELLENT COMTEMPORARY GOSPEL BLUEGRASS CONCERT!!! I WOULD GIVE IT 10 STARS IF I COULD. IF YOU ARE NOT FAMILIAR WITH THIS GROUP, AND YOU LIKE GOSPEL BLUEGRASS - YOU MUST SEE THIS CONCERT DVD AND THIER OTHER ONE. THIS FAMILY & THEIR BAND ARE SIMPLE "AWESOME". THIS PARTICULAR CONCERT DVD IS A "MUST-HAVE" FOR ANY GOSPEL BLUEGRASS FAN!!!YOU GET 4 BASIC MUSICIANS IN THE FAMILY, THE MOTHER (LILY ON VOCALS), TWO SISTERS(SONYA ON VOCALS AND MANDOLIN & REBECCA ON GUITAR AND VOCALS), AND  A BROTHER (BEN ON BASS). PLUS, YOU GET A HOST OF OTHER BACKUP MUSICIANS INCLUDING A VIOLIN PLAYER, A BANJO PLAYER, AND OTHERS THESE PEOPLE CAN DEFINITELY PLAY GOSPEL BLUEGRASS. REBECCA'S HUSBAND WAS IN THE BAND IN THEIR LAST DVD "THE ISSAC'S BEST OF THE HOMECOMING SERIES", BUT NOW HE IS IN THE AUIDIENCE IN THIS DVD (THEY SAY HE QUIT THE BAND TO BECOME A SCHOOL TEACHER).THE SONGS INCLUDE:GREAT IS THY REWARDIF THAT DON'T MAKE YOU WANT TO GOI SURRENDER ALLYOURS AND MINEI'LL FLY AWAYWALK ON (THIS IS OUTSTANDING - YOU MUST WATCH THIS ONE, IF YOU DO -YOU'LL BE 'HOOKED' ON THE ISSACS. ALSO, IN THIS SONG THEY SEEM TO BE MAKING A REFERENCE ABOUT THE LEGENDARY BLUESMAN, ROBERT JOHNSON AND THE "STORY?" ABOUT HIM SELLING HIS SOUL TO THE DEVIL AT THE CROSSROADS - THEY SING IF THE DEVIL IS AT THE CROSSROADS TRYING TO MAKE YOU A DEAL - THEN WALK ON!!! (DON'T TURN TO THE RIGHT OR TURN TO THE LEFT, JUST WALK ON!!!) (THIS ONE HAS BEEN ON THE COMTEMPORARY SOUTHERN GOSPEL CHARTS FOR WEEKS, IT'S A GREAT HIT!!!)BARBIE BANDAIDS (ABOUT CHILDREN GROWING UP)THROUGH THE VALLEYIT IS WELL WITH MY SOUL (THERE'S A STORY BEHIND THIS SONG ALSO!)I BRING IT TO YOUHE TOUCHED MEHEROES (ABOUT SPECIAL NEEDS CHILDREN)THAT'S ALRIGHT BY MEFREIND TO THE ENDLOVE IS A CROSS YOU BEARTHE OLD RUGGED CROSSTHE ONE I'M DYING FORTHE LOVE OF GODHE AIN'T NEVER DONE ME NOTHIN' BUT GOOD (A EXCELLENT END ALL SONG!!!!)THIS IS COMTEMPORARY GOSPEL BLUEGRASS AT ITS VERY BEST, SO IF YOU LIKE THIS KINDA MUSIC, YOU'LL ENJOY THIS ONE, AND IN THAT CONTEXT, I HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT!!!
summary: THE ISAACS - LIVE FROM NORWAY - DVD - OUTSTANDING CONTEMPORARY GOSPEL BLUEGRASS!!!

reviewText: The Issacs are a fantastic group that will not fail to please. The amazing portion where the Grandma speaks about her time in the Nazi death camp is very moving and a great addition to this DVD. The beautiful voices, the tour of Denmark and the personal touches, like the "make-up" demonstration in "Special Features" make this a DVD you will enjoy over and over.
summary: Awesome Gaither DVD, One of the best!
